"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/932750","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-07-09","<p>On 13 June 2018 the Parliamentary Under Secretary of State for Health (Lord O’Shaughnessy) and officials had an introductory meeting with GW Pharmaceuticals, which develops licensed medicines containing ingredients derived from cannabis, during which the benefits of that company’s medicines were discussed.</p><p> </p><p>The Medicines and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency is responsible for the regulation of medicines in the United Kingdom and has provided advice and guidance, on request, to companies developing cannabis-based medicinal products, to support specific medical indications in relation to potential future marketing authorisation applications for new medicines.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-07-09T14:45:09.503Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/932750/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/932750/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/932750/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-29","Cannabis: Medical Treatments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what discussions his Department has had with representatives of the medicinal cannabis industry on the medicinal and therapeutic benefits of (a) cannabis and (b) cannabis-based medicinal products.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","158986"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/932751","Scotland Office","false","2018-07-04","<p>I have regular discussions with Cabinet colleagues and the Scottish Government on a range of business issues. I am aware of the concerning situation at Havelock Europa and my officials are in touch directly with the relevant parties on this matter.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2018-07-04T09:47:17.003Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/932751/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/932751/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/932751/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2018-06-29","Havelock Europa: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, whether he has had discussions with (a) Havelock Europa, (b) The Scottish Government and (c) Cabinet colleagues on the (i) financial situation of Havelock Europa and (ii) protection of the rights of workers at that company.","false","Biography information for Lesley Laird","Kirkcaldy and Cowdenbeath","Lesley Laird","159062"
